10 Aug 2016Johannesburg, Wednesday 10 August 2016 Media are invited to join the Minister of Communications, Ms Faith Muthambi at the inaugural Nation Brand Forum hosted by Brand South Africa, on Wednesday 24 August 2016 at the Maslow Hotel in Sandton. One of the key strategic imperatives for Brand South Africa, is to proactively develop strategies that will shape and build the country image and reputation, in order to coherently articulate the nation brand identity. It is within this context that Brand South Africa, will engage with stakeholders from government, civil society and the private sector to identify the country s strengths which will anchor a common approach on how to position South Africa as a globally competitive nation brand in a cohesive and consistent manner.Media is invited to attend as follows: Date: Wednesday 24 August 2016 Time: 08h30 15h00 Venue: The Maslow Hotel, 46 Rivonia Rd, Sandton, 2146 RSVPS/Enquiries: Tsabeng Nthite Email: tsabengn@brandsouthafrica.com Mobile number: 076 371 6810Media are kindly requested to RSVP by Tuesday 16 August 2016 for logistical reasons. Brand South Africa will also be able to facilitate any requests for interviews. Follow the conversation on #SANationBrand Programme for the Brand South Africa Nation Brand Forum08:30-09:00 Arrival &amp; registration All 09:00-09:05 Opening 5 Minute AV profiling the strengths of South Africa 09:05-09:15 Background to the Nation Brand Forum Brand South Africa Chairperson of the Board of Trustees, Ms Khanyisile Thandiwe Kweyama 09:15-09:45 Keynote Address Hon. Minister of Communications, Faith Muthambi 09:45-10:05 Nation Brand Performance Brand South Africa General Manager: Research , Brand South Africa, Dr. Petrus de Kock 10:05-10:25 Building String Sustainable Brands Brand Specialist 10:25-10:30 Briefing on Breakaway Workshop Groups Brand South Africa s Chief Marketing Officer, Mrs. Linda Magapatona-Sangaret 10:30-10:45 Tea/Coffee Break All 10:45-12:30 Breakaway Sessions All 11:00-12:30 Facilitation of Media Interviews Communications and Media 12:30-13:30 Lunch Ms Sithembile Ntombela, General Manager: Marketing, Brand SA 13:30-14:45 Feedback Session All 14:45-15:00 Wrap up and Closing Remarks Brand South Africa s CEO, Mr Kingsley MakhubelaNotes to the Editor About Brand South Africa Brand South Africa is the official marketing agency of South Africa, with a mandate to build the country's brand reputation, in order to improve its global competitiveness. Its aim is also to build pride and patriotism among South Africans, in order to contribute to social cohesion and nation brand ambassadorship.About Play Your Part Play Your Part is a nationwide programme created to inspire, empower and celebrate active citizenship in South Africa. It aims to lift the spirit of our nation by inspiring all South Africans to contribute to positive change, become involved and start doing. A nation of people who care deeply for one another and the environment in which they live is good for everyone.Play Your Part is aimed at all South Africans from corporates and individuals, NGOs and government, churches and schools, from the young to the not-so-young. It aims to encourage South Africans to use some of their time, money, skills or goods to contribute to a better future for all.Join the conversation at: Join the conversation BrandSouthAfrica @Brand_SAFor more information or to set up interviews, please contact: Tsabeng Nthite Tel: +27 11 712 5061 Mobile: +27 (0) 76 371 6810 Email:tsabengn@brandsouthafrica.com Visit www.brandsouthafrica.com